The paper discusses the development of a modular control architecture for autonomous underwater vehicles (AUVs) to efficiently manage mission time in a realistic ocean environment. The paper focuses on motion planning and mission scheduling, which are key areas of research in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for the AUV to make robust decisions and be aware of its environment, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper mentions the use of optimization algorithms, which are commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
